                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/101b.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Vice
                        Consul <persName type="to">Simpich</persName>.</hi>
                    <note n="134" xml:id="d1483fn134">Same to Consul Edwards.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 21, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>British Ambassador communicates telegram from Mrs. Benton praying that her
                    husband’s body be recovered before decomposition sets in. Endeavor to secure
                    compliance with this request.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
